commit_list.message: Moved the setting of the PWM duty cycle to the PWM task.
Showing fan power usage instead of current. Read the assignment!
Moved alive task to it's own module.

Cleaned up some redundant init.
Moved some to the right modules.
Set up CPU.
Better mA calculation. Still a rough estimate, though.
Numbers will now not show leading zeroes.
Added showing of the fans RPM.

Added interrupt for the encoder.
Added calcualtion of RPM.
Added showing of the current. Current will onlu update every CURRENT_UPDATE_DELAY times the controller task is run.
Added current reading with setup of the ADC.
Added init and task to fan module.

Added init and duty cycle method for PWM.
Sometimes the fan refuses to start. I hev no idea why.
Added PWM & fan tasks to RTCS.

Removed some unused code.
Reused a variable.

Added min/max-speed defines.
Added a set-speed method.

Added the module for the pot.
Included initialization code, task and methods for getting the value.
The value will be given between 0 and 100.
Added prototypes for the de/increase methods for fan ref-speed.
Changed max ref-speed to 100. Down from 255.
Adjusting the fan ref-speed with the digiswitch now works.
Got rid of a few extra spaces. Yay OCD!
Changing state to DIG will now zero the counter so we don't get a change-value from when the state was POT.
Bug fix. Will now update the LCD properly.
Added prototyopes of the two methods for adding strings and chars to the .h file.
Controller will now show the fan REF speed on the LCD.
Added a getter for the fan ref. speed.

Controller will now switch states when the digibutton is pressed.
Showing the state on the LCD.
Added controlle init & task to RTCS.
Added speed_up and speed_down methods to fan.c
Added fan.c/.h files for controlling of the fan.

Updated lcd.c to use dirty bits and only change a character that was actually changed in the buffer since the last update.
This way the LCD will update much more rapidly than before.
Updated RTC to start at 00 hours in stead of 11.
Added the projetc-file and debug files to ignore-list.
Deleted a space to test GitX.
Added the code from rpevious. Spaghetti-code mostly.
Added README, thin though it may be.
Added marker to the Decision maker. and cam marker Node.
Added start-mode parameter to the wii-state node.
Changed default wii state to Drive.
Teh decisionmake now stops when ordered by the wii state. (Hopefully)
Added blinking LED to the Wiimote and a drive/stop state on the A-button
Small change to minus sign in turning. This commit has a working headland drive
changes made when testing PID on Hilde
Added a few more informations to the state message.
Object avoidance ndoe now subscribe to the wheel-speeds as well.
Hilde will now actually move at the max speed set in linear_mean_speed-parameter.
Upped mean-speed and made Hilde slow down at the end of the row.
Not the best, but it works
Added detection of obstacles in turn-state.

Decisionmake now finds the ends of the rows as they
can be seen in the row/boxes.
Added detection of rows with boxes.
Added visualized boxes for the left row as well.
Changed code faults while testing hilde
Added decisions based on the object avoidance
Small changes to queues, to get the robot running.
Row distance and angle detection working.
Hild is running now with IMU, LRS and a castor wheel.
Added calcualtion for actual wheel velocities.
Work done on getting a headingf rom the compass.
New hildecontroller with encoder feedback enabled.
Moved a few parameters out into the launch file.
Started on enabling PID control of the wheels.

IMU node can now communicate
over local topics.

Added the Sparkfun 9DOF
parser from Frobolab.
Started on getting the individual wheel speeds.
Commented out some stuff that didn't compile.
Small change to use Joy instead of sensor_msgs
New old files from Morten. Getting rid of all changes from Frobolab.
Small change to the IMU node to use a global namehandler (I think) ins tead of a global one. It screwed up the namespaces
Data is now published from the IMU node.

Changed to float values as that suits
the data better.

Some of the IMU parser done.
It will now set the IMU to teh correct
data type and receive the data.

Changed the readhandler function to an
older version so it doesn't chop up strings
from the IMU.

Added a IMU parser node along with a msg
or the data gotten from the IMU.

The included ROS IMU msg does not have
room for the compass data, so I decided
to make a new one.

The parser is running and getting data
from the serial node.
Small change for Morten to try out Gits awesomeness.

Change the errorchecking of the serial_node a bit.
I kept getting eof() warnings. I don't think that
is bad as we will always reach the end of the "file".
